<eesti>Eesti Vabariigi t&ouml;&ouml;lepingu seaduse (RT 1992, 15/16, 241; 1993, 10, 150; RT I 1993, 26, 441; 1995, 14, 170; 16, 228; 1996, 3, 57; 40, 773; 45, 850; 49, 953; 1997, 5/6, 32) &sect;-d 62 ja 63 muudetakse ja s&otilde;nastatakse j&auml;rgmiselt: </eesti>
<inglise>Sections 62 and 63 of the Republic of Estonia Employment Contracts Act (RT 1992, 15/16, 241; 1993, 10, 150; RT I 1993, 26, 441; 1995, 14, 170; 16, 228; 1996, 3, 57; 40, 773; 45, 850; 49, 953; 1997, 5/6, 32) are amended and worded as follows: </inglise>
<eesti>"&sect; 62. </eesti>
<inglise>"&sect; 62. </inglise>
<eesti>T&ouml;&ouml;taja n&otilde;udmisel tema t&ouml;&ouml;tingimuste ajutine kergendamine v&otilde;i ajutine &uuml;leviimine teisele t&ouml;&ouml;le </eesti>
<inglise>Temporary easement of working conditions or temporary transfer to other position at request of employee </inglise>
<eesti>(1) T&ouml;&ouml;tajal on arsti vormistatud haiguslehe alusel &otilde;igus t&ouml;&ouml;andjalt n&otilde;uda t&ouml;&ouml;tingimuste ajutist kergendamist v&otilde;i ajutist &uuml;leviimist terviseseisundile vastavale t&ouml;&ouml;le. </eesti>
<inglise>(1) An employee has the right to request from the employer temporary easement of working conditions or temporary transfer to a position suitable to the employee's state of health based on a certificate for sick leave prepared by a doctor. </inglise>
<eesti>(2) T&ouml;&ouml;tingimuste ajutise kergendamise v&otilde;i terviseseisundile vastavale t&ouml;&ouml;le &uuml;leviimise tagaj&auml;rjel tekkinud palgavahe h&uuml;vitatakse t&ouml;&ouml;tajale Eesti Vabariigi ravikindlustusseaduses (RT 1991, 23, 272; 1992, 19, 276; RT I 1994, 23, 387; 1997, 28, 425; 1998, 111, 1829) s&auml;testatud korras, v&auml;lja arvatud k&auml;esoleva paragrahvi 3. l&otilde;ikes etten&auml;htud juhtudel. </eesti>
<inglise>(2) The difference in wages resulting from temporary easement of working conditions or temporary transfer to a position suitable to the state of health shall be compensated to the employee pursuant to the procedure provided for in the Republic of Estonia Health Insurance Act (RT 1991, 23, 272; 1992, 19, 276; RT I 1994, 23, 387; 1997, 28, 425; 1998, 111, 1829), except in the cases prescribed in subsection (3) of this section. </inglise>
<eesti>(3) T&ouml;&ouml;taja vabastatakse haiguslehel etten&auml;htud ajaks t&ouml;&ouml;st, kui t&ouml;&ouml;andja asukoha (elukoha) j&auml;rgne t&ouml;&ouml;inspektor on tuvastanud, et t&ouml;&ouml;andjal ei ole v&otilde;imalik t&ouml;&ouml;tingimusi ajutiselt kergendada v&otilde;i t&ouml;&ouml;tajat terviseseisundile vastavale t&ouml;&ouml;le ajutiselt &uuml;le viia. </eesti>
<inglise>(3) The employee shall be released from work for the period prescribed in the certificate for sick leave if the labour inspector of the seat (residence) of the employer establishes that it is not possible for the employer to ease the working conditions temporarily or transfer the employee temporarily to a position suitable to his or her state of health. </inglise>
<eesti>T&ouml;&ouml;st vabastamise aja eest makstakse t&ouml;&ouml;tajale kohustusliku ravikindlustuse h&uuml;vitist Eesti Vabariigi ravikindlustusseaduses etten&auml;htud korras. </eesti>
<inglise>A mandatory medical insurance benefit shall be paid to the employee for the period of release from work pursuant to the procedure prescribed in the Republic of Estonia Health Insurance Act. </inglise>
<eesti>&sect; 63. </eesti>
<inglise>&sect; 63. </inglise>
<eesti>Raseda t&ouml;&ouml;tingimuste ajutine kergendamine v&otilde;i ajutine &uuml;leviimine teisele t&ouml;&ouml;le </eesti>
<inglise>Temporary easement of working conditions or temporary transfer to another position of pregnant women </inglise>
<eesti>(1) Rasedal on &otilde;igus n&otilde;uda arsti vormistatud haiguslehe alusel t&ouml;&ouml;tingimuste ajutist kergendamist v&otilde;i ajutist &uuml;leviimist teisele t&ouml;&ouml;le. </eesti>
<inglise>(1) Pregnant women have the right to request temporary easement of working conditions or temporary transfer to another position based on a certificate for sick leave prepared by a doctor. </inglise>
<eesti>T&ouml;&ouml;tajale h&uuml;vitatakse palgavahe Eesti Vabariigi ravikindlustusseaduses etten&auml;htud korras. </eesti>
<inglise>The difference in wages shall be compensated to the employee pursuant to the procedure prescribed in the Republic of Estonia Health Insurance Act. </inglise>
<eesti>(2) Kui t&ouml;&ouml;andja asukoha (elukoha) j&auml;rgne t&ouml;&ouml;inspektor on tuvastanud, et t&ouml;&ouml;andjal ei ole v&otilde;imalik raseda t&ouml;&ouml;tingimusi kergendada v&otilde;i teda kergemale t&ouml;&ouml;le &uuml;le viia, vabastatakse ta haiguslehel n&auml;idatud ajaks t&ouml;&ouml;st ja makstakse kohustusliku ravikindlustuse h&uuml;vitist Eesti Vabariigi ravikindlustusseaduses etten&auml;htud korras." </eesti>
<inglise>(2) If the labour inspector of the seat (residence) of the employer establishes that it is not possible for the employer to ease the working conditions of the pregnant woman or transfer her to an easier job, she shall be released from work for the period prescribed in the certificate for sick leave and paid a mandatory medical insurance benefit pursuant to the procedure prescribed in the Republic of Estonia Health Insurance Act." </inglise>
<eesti>&sect; 3. </eesti>
<inglise>&sect; 3. </inglise>
<eesti>Avaliku teenistuse seaduse (RT I 1995, 16, 228; 50, 764; 97, 1664; 1996, 15, 265; 45, 850; 1997, 1, 4; 29, 447; 1998, 34, 486; 38, 563; 41/42, 625; 50, 753; 57, 858; 110, 1809) &sect; 51 muudetakse ja s&otilde;nastatakse j&auml;rgmiselt: </eesti>
<inglise>Section 51 of the Public Service Act (RT I 1995, 16, 228; 50, 764; 97, 1664; 1996, 15, 265; 45, 850; 1997, 1, 4; 29, 447; 1998, 34, 486; 38, 563; 41/42, 625; 50, 753; 57, 858; 110, 1809) is amended and worded as follows: </inglise>
<eesti>"&sect; 51. </eesti>
<inglise>"&sect; 51. </inglise>
<eesti>Ametniku teenistustingimuste ajutine kergendamine ja ametniku ajutine &uuml;leviimine raseduse ajaks </eesti>
<inglise>Temporary easement of conditions of service and temporary transfer of official during pregnancy </inglise>
<eesti>(1) Ametnikul on tema raseduse ajaks arsti vormistatud haiguslehe alusel &otilde;igus teenistustingimuste ajutisele kergendamisele v&otilde;i ajutisele &uuml;leviimisele teisele ametikohale, v&auml;lja arvatud konkursi korras t&auml;idetavale ametikohale. </eesti>
<inglise>(1) During pregnancy, an official shall be entitled, based on a certificate for sick leave prepared by a doctor, to the temporary easement of her conditions of service or to a temporary transfer to another position, except a position to be filled by way of competition. </inglise>
<eesti>Palgavahe h&uuml;vitatakse Eesti Vabariigi ravikindlustusseaduses (RT 1991, 23, 272; 1999, 7, 113) s&auml;testatud korras. </eesti>
<inglise>The difference in wages shall be compensated pursuant to the procedure provided for in the Republic of Estonia Health Insurance Act (RT 1991, 23, 272; 1999, 7, 113). </inglise>
<eesti>(2) K&auml;esoleva paragrahvi 1. l&otilde;ikes s&auml;testatud teenistustingimuste kergendamise v&otilde;i &uuml;leviimise v&otilde;imatuse korral vabastatakse ametnik haiguslehel n&auml;idatud ajaks ameti&uuml;lesannete t&auml;itmisest ja makstakse kohustusliku ravikindlustuse h&uuml;vitist Eesti Vabariigi ravikindlustusseaduses etten&auml;htud korras." </eesti>
<inglise>(2) If the easement of conditions of service or transfer provided for in subsection (1) of this section is impossible, an official shall be released from the performance of her functions for the period prescribed in the certificate for sick leave and shall be paid a mandatory medical insurance benefit pursuant to the procedure prescribed in the Republic of Estonia Health Insurance Act." </inglise>
<eesti>&sect; 4. </eesti>
<inglise>&sect; 4. </inglise>
<eesti>Riigil&otilde;ivuseaduse (RT I 1997, 80, 1344; 86, 1461; 87, 1466 ja 1467; 93, 1563; 1998, 2, 47; 4, 63; 23, 321; 36/37, 552 ja 553; 52/53, 771; 57, 859; 59, 941; 60, 951; 61, 979 ja 985; 64/65, 1004, 1005 ja 1008; 86/87, 1408; 97, 1519; 103, 1701; 108/109, 1783) &sect; 16 l&otilde;iget 1 t&auml;iendatakse punktiga 15 j&auml;rgmises s&otilde;nastuses: </eesti>
<inglise>Subsection 16 (1) of the State Fees Act (RT I 1997, 80, 1344; 86, 1461; 87, 1466 and 1467; 93, 1563; 1998, 2, 47; 4, 63; 23, 321; 36/37, 552 and 553; 52/53, 771; 57, 859; 59, 941; 60, 951; 61, 979 and 985; 64/65, 1004, 1005 and 1008; 86/87, 1408; 97, 1519; 103, 1701; 108/109, 1783) is amended by adding clause 15) worded as follows: </inglise>
<eesti>"15) haigekassad raviteenuste ja kohustusliku ravikindlustuse h&uuml;vitiste summade sissen&otilde;ude asjades." </eesti>
<inglise>"15) health insurance funds, in matters concerning claims for payment of amounts for health services and mandatory medical insurance benefits." </inglise>
<eesti>&sect; 5. </eesti>
<inglise>&sect; 5. </inglise>
<eesti>Rakenduss&auml;tted </eesti>
<inglise>Implementing provisions </inglise>
<eesti>(1) K&auml;esolev seadus j&otilde;ustub 1999. aasta 1. jaanuaril. </eesti>
<inglise>(1) This Act enters into force on 1 January 1999. </inglise>
<eesti>(1 (1)) Eesti Vabariigi ravikindlustusseaduse &sect; 2 l&otilde;ikes 2 loetletud isikutega v&otilde;rdsustatakse 1999. aasta 1. jaanuarist kuni 1. aprillini ka j&auml;rgmised isikud: </eesti>
<inglise>(1 (1)) From 1 January 1999 to 1 April 1999, the following persons shall have equal status to the persons set out in subsection 2 (2) of the Republic of Estonia Health Insurance Act: </inglise>
<eesti>1) kuni 3-aastase lapsega lapsehoolduspuhkusel olev isik v&otilde;i mittet&ouml;&ouml;tav, kuni 3-aastast last kasvatav &uuml;ks vanem; </eesti>
<inglise>1) persons on parental leave with a child of up to 3 years of age, or one non-working parent raising a child of up to 3 years of age; </inglise>
<eesti>2) v&auml;lisesinduses t&ouml;&ouml;tava diplomaadi mittet&ouml;&ouml;tav abikaasa; </eesti>
<inglise>2) non-working spouses of diplomats serving in foreign missions; </inglise>
<eesti>3) kaitsej&otilde;ududes ajateenistuses olev ajateenija; </eesti>
<inglise>3) conscripts in the compulsory service of the Defence Forces; </inglise>
<eesti>4) invaliidide &uuml;hingu tootmisettev&otilde;ttes (tulumaksuseaduse &sect; 5 l&otilde;ike 1 punkti 3 m&otilde;istes) t&ouml;&ouml;tav invaliid; </eesti>
<inglise>4) disabled persons working in a manufacturing enterprise of an association of disabled persons (as defined in clause 5 (1) 3) of the Income Tax Act); </inglise>
<eesti>5) t&ouml;&ouml;tuna arvel olev isik. </eesti>
<inglise>5) persons registered as unemployed. </inglise>
<eesti>(16.12.98 j&otilde;ust. 01.01.99 - RT I 1998, 113/114, 1876) </eesti>
<inglise>(16.12.98 entered into force 01.01.99 RT I 1998, 113/114, 1876) </inglise>
<eesti>(2) Eesti Vabariigi ravikindlustusseaduse &sect; 10 l&otilde;iget 1 rakendatakse nende t&ouml;&ouml;v&otilde;imetuslehtede osas, mis esitatakse kohustusliku ravikindlustuse h&uuml;vitise m&auml;&auml;ramiseks ja maksmiseks p&auml;rast 1999. aasta 1. jaanuari. </eesti>
<inglise>(2) Subsection 10 (1) of the Republic of Estonia Health Insurance Act applies to certificates of incapacity for work which are submitted for the grant and payment of mandatory medical insurance benefits after 1 January 1999. </inglise>
<eesti>(3) Kuni 2000. aasta 1. juulini v&otilde;ib haigekassa korraldada h&uuml;vitise ja palgavahe m&auml;&auml;ramist ja maksmist t&ouml;&ouml;andjate kaudu. </eesti>
<inglise>(3) Until 1 July 2000, the health insurance fund may organise the grant and payment of benefits and differences in wages through employers. </inglise>
<eesti>(4) Vabariigi Valitsus tagab k&auml;esoleva seaduse j&otilde;ustumisest &uuml;he kuu jooksul Eesti Vabariigi ravikindlustusseaduse tervikteksti avaldamise Riigi Teatajas koos k&otilde;igi tehtud muudatuste ja t&auml;iendustega. </eesti>
<inglise>(4) The Government of the Republic shall ensure publication of the consolidated text of the Republic of Estonia Health Insurance Act together with all amendments made thereto in the Riigi Teataja within one month after the entry into force of this Act. </inglise>
